				<td colspan="2"><span>mobs do not mitigate (for example) all slows by 30%. The way it works is mobs who mitigate slow can be slowed to a MAx of (for example) 30%.
<br />

<br />
Lets say my Requiem is a 50% slow and shaman slow is 75%. A mob who mitigates all slows up to 50% will mitgate the shaman slow, but not the bard slow. If a mob mitigates slows to 10% it will mitigate both slows and both slows will land for only 10%. 
<br />

<br />
This is why shamans are so annoyed because many mobs can be slowed just as well by a beastlord or bard, than a shaman.
<br />

<br />

<br />
This is just from personal experience. Its also very possible that therejust IS a bug =) Ioften land slows with no mitigation message where shamans get the message. Never asked one to throw a lower level slow on them tho to test.</span></td>
